    "summary": "I have a strong belief in the added value high quality communications can bring to companies, organizations and people. My specialties are the end-to-end creation of communication strategies, content and events and orchestrating the implementation and execution of these in close cooperation with the executives and communications teams inside the organization. Key focus areas are strategic (company strategy, business performance, cultures and values, performance management), transformational (reorganizations, integration, lay-offs, outsourcing, mergers and acquisitions, etc) and employee and leadership communications. I am multi-lingual and have a global mindset. I lived in the Netherlands, Finland and Germany and worked and traveled across all continents for global companies. \n\nI've worked over 30 years inside businesses during which I gained a wide range of experience:\n\u2022\tEmployee and management communications in complex, international business environments. I have been working with CEO\u2019s and Board members of listed and non-listed companies in the financial, telecommunications and technical industries.\n\u2022\tYears of experience in external communications as well, mainly in product and consumer communications in the financial industry. \n\u2022\tStrong capabilities in planning and developing communications strategies and events, managing communications budget, working with a huge variety of communications channels, from traditional print to email letters and internal social media like Yammer. \n\u2022\tManagerial experience with highly talented teams in the communications function, with a strong focus on executing the communications strategy to add value to companies and continuously strive for innovation of the function and communications infrastructure. \n\u2022\tTraining and coaching experience in improving the communications skills of line managers who need to translate and explain company strategies, all sorts of changes and transformations to their direct reports. ",
